INSTALLATION

1.OSGi

If you want install the OSGi introspector into an OSGi platform, you must installed the two bundles with the "start" command of the OSGi console.

2.Eclipse

Into Eclipse, it's just necessary to add these two bundles into the folder "plugins" on the Eclipse installation location.


USE

Dynamic Introspector :
---------------------
	ServiceReference refs = context.getServiceReference(OSGiIntrospectorDynamic.class.getName());
	if (refs != null) {
		OSGiIntrospectorDynamic introspector = (OSGiIntrospectorDynamic)context.getService(refs);
		introspector.introspect(<destination>, <boolean>);
	}
	
If you want modelize the resources available into the bundle, <boolean> must be true.
<destination> is a String which define where the model.

Static Introspector :
---------------------
There are two way to use the Static Introspector.

1.Into an OSGi platform

ServiceReference refs = context.getServiceReference(OSGiIntrospectorStatic.class.getName());
	if (refs != null) {
		OSGiIntrospectorStatic introspector = (OSGiIntrospectorStatic)context.getService(refs);
		introspector.generateFramework(<frameworkFolder>,<destination>, <boolean>);
	}

2.Into a standard application

OSGiIntrospectorStatic introspector = new OSGiIntrospectorStatic(new OSGiIntrospectorUtilStatic());
introspector.generateFramework(<frameworkFolder>,<destination>, <boolean>);

If you want modelize the resources available into the bundle, <boolean> must be true.
<destination> is a String which define where the model.
<frameworkFolder> is a String which is the path of a file which contains all the bundle of the framework.